        "created_at": "2026-01-01T17:09:49.936Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Letâ€™s encrypt recently started supporting issuing TLS certificates not only for DNS names, but also for <a href=\"https://letsencrypt.org/2025/07/01/issuing-our-first-ip-address-certificate\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">IP addresses</a> using the <a href=\"https://letsencrypt.org/docs/profiles/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">shortlived profile</a>.</p>\n<p>That should make it possible to setup Signal TLS proxies that have no domain name, but only a public IP. This would reduce effort and costs to run a proxy.</p>\n<p>The feature I request would be that the Signal clients start supporting IP-only proxies.<br>\nAdditionally the <a href=\"https://github.com/signalapp/Signal-TLS-Proxy\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Signal TLS Proxy repo</a> should be updated to document and allow automated setup of such proxies, similar as for domain-based proxies today.</p>",
