        "created_at": "2026-01-16T19:50:43.214Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Now Letâ€™s Encrypt has also published a blog post announcing the general availability IP Address Certificates</p>\n<aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\" data-onebox-src=\"https://letsencrypt.org/2026/01/15/6day-and-ip-general-availability\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://letsencrypt.org/2026/01/15/6day-and-ip-general-availability\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">letsencrypt.org</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"aspect-image\" style=\"--aspect-ratio:690/362;\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/c/0/c0f71b11acf471cb0064575038886ed2fcc9a16b_2_690x362.png\" class=\"thumbnail\" alt=\"\" data-dominant-color=\"DEE4E8\" width=\"690\" height=\"362\"></div>\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://letsencrypt.org/2026/01/15/6day-and-ip-general-availability\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">6-day and IP Address Certificates are Generally Available</a></h3>\n\n  <p>Short-lived and IP address certificates are now generally available from Letâ€™s Encrypt. These certificates are valid for 160 hours, just over six days. In order to get a short-lived certificate subscribers simply need to select the â€˜shortlivedâ€™...</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n",
